\tan \dfrac{3\pi}{8}=1+\sqrt2
|z_1|=|z_2|=|z_3|=1
\arg z_1=\frac{\pi}{2}, \arg z_2=\frac{\pi}{4},\arg z_3=\pi
\tan{\frac{3 \pi}{8}} = \frac{\sin{(3 \pi/8)}}{\cos{(3 \pi/8)}} = \sqrt{\frac{1-\cos{(3 \pi/4)}}{1+\cos{(3 \pi/4)}}} = \sqrt{\frac{2+\sqrt{2}}{2-\sqrt{2}}} = \frac{2+\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{2}} = \sqrt{2}+1
z_1 + z_2
\tan(\operatorname{arg}z) = \frac{\operatorname{Im} z}{\operatorname{Re} z}.
